Mamedyarov, Shakhriyar (2716) - Suleymanli, Aydin (2553) *
FIDE World Blitz Chess Championship 2023 (Chess.com) [10] 2023.12.29
A45 Trompovsky attack (Ruth, Opovcensky opening)

1.d4 Nf6 2.Bg5 d5 3.Nd2 c5 4.dxc5 e6 5.e4 Bxc5 6.e5 Qb6 7.exf6 Bxf2+ 8.Ke2 Bxg1 9.Rxg1 Qxg1 10.Ne4 Rg8 11.fxg7 Rxg7 12.Qd2 h6 13.Qc3 hxg5 14.Qxc8+ Ke7 15.Nf2 Nc6 16.Qxb7+ Kd6 17.Qxa8 Nd4+ 18.Ke3 Nf5+ 19.Ke2 Nd4+ 20.Kd3 Qxf2 21.Qb8+ Kc6 22.Rc1 Qf5+ 23.Kxd4 Qe4+ 24.Kc3 Qe3+ 25.Bd3 d4+ 26.Kb3 Qxc1 27.Be4+ Kd7 28.Qxa7+ Ke8 29.Bc6+ Kf8 30.Qb8+ Ke7 31.Qe8+ Kf6 32.Qd8+ Kg6 33.Qxd4 f5 34.Qe5 Re7 35.a4 Qd2 36.a5 Qd8 37.Ka2 Qc8 38.Ba4 Rc7 39.b4 Rc4 40.Qb2 Qa6 41.Ka3 Re4 42.Bb3 Qb5 43.Qc3 f4 44.Ba4 Qa6 45.Qc5 Re3+ 46.Bb3 e5 47.Kb2 Kh5 48.Qb6 Qc8 49.Qc5 Qf5 50.a6 Re1 51.a7 Qg4

Timestamps:
00:00 Hello Everyone!

The FIDE World Rapid Championship is a 13-round Swiss tournament taking place from 26–28 December 2022 in Almaty, Kazakhstan. The prize fund is $350,000, with a $60,000 top prize.

Players receive 15 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. A tie for 1st is decided by two 3+2 blitz games. If still tied, more 3+2 games are played until a player wins. Official website: worldrapidandblitz2022.fide.com
